title: Fan, 1820–50
creditline: Gift of Mrs. George B. McClellan
description: Leaf - paper obverse, two scenes in colored lithograph - a lady with her pet birds etc., and a lady visiting a fortune teller - remainder of obverse decorated with gold arabesques on a blue field, putti, devils - reverse bears three chinoiseries in gilt and black - sticks are of pierced ivory

tombstone.epitaph:
Fan, 1820–50.
1820–50. Medium: ivory and paper. Gift of Mrs. George B. McClellan. 1935-2-5-a.
